<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-11-11T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-11-11T16:00:00-05:00" n="736" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d736">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/6612:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Leopoldville</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Mallon</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leopoldville</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-11T22:00:00+01:00">November 11, 1940—10 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received November 12—10:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Referring to my telegram dated October 31. Libreville taken by De
                                Gaulle forces November 10 by air and sea attack. General Tetu taken
                                prisoner. De Gaulle reports very little bloodshed, insists that no
                                British forces took part, sees possibility of retaliatory measures
                                against Pointe-Noire and Fort Lamy by Dakar troops.</p>
                            <p>The Governor General of the Belgian Congo gave a very strong
                                pro-British pro-De Gaulle Armistice Day address.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mallon</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>